I would definitely look for other companies than this one. I took my dog to been seen for a swollen eye, she was treated for infection 2 different times. Then she continued to have trouble and was diagnosed with Entropion that requires surgery. The policy states you pay 20% for surgery and they pay the 80%. That is false, they only pay up to your per pet incident which my per incident was $500. Her surgery was $1800 they paid 120.22 because they said that they had already paid out $377.78 when she was treated for the swollen eye. So don't fall for the surgery being covered. They are very deceiving and I would stay away! 
This is what is in the contract:
What is Covered
After satisfying the annual Deductible indicated on the Declarations Page, We will reimburse You in accordance with Your plan, less
any limitations and exclusions, the amount after Coinsurance for eligible Covered Expenses that are Medically Necessary to treat or
diagnose a current covered Incident showing Symptoms during the Policy period but after the Waiting Period, including but not limited
to:
a. Laboratory tests, x-rays, ultrasound, MRI and CT scans;
b. Surgery;
c. Hospitalization
d. Prescription Medication that is prescribed by a Veterinarian;
e. Extractions to permanent broken teeth due to an Accident;
f. Chemotherapy;
g. Hydrotherapy and Physical Therapy;
h. Emergency ground Pet Ambulance transportation up to the maximum benefit for this coverage as specified on the
Declarations Page; and
i. Euthanasia (when advised by a Veterinarian to alleviate suffering).
